The wrong 'un and Rohit read it well, came down the track, got close to the pitch and was then looking to launch it back over the bowler's end. Unfortunately for him, the bat turned slightly on impact and he ended up heaving it down the throat of Tewatia at long-on - didn't have to move an inch and the Royals have their man. Rohit c Rahul Tewatia b Shreyas Gopal 35(23) [4s-2 6s-3]

Commentary Text: Bumrah to Shreyas Gopal, out Caught by de Kock! Oh this is Vintage Bumrah. Maybe Bumrah isn't old enough for the word VIintage to be associated with him, so lets say "typical" Bumrah! Angling in sharply, brute-forcing even this unresponsive Kookaburra to straighten off the seam, and take the hopping batsman's outside edge to the 'keeper for a catch. QdK just about keeps that off his face. Might consider a helmet. Shreyas Gopal c de Kock b Bumrah 1(2)

Commentary Text: Rahul Chahar to Lomror, out Caught by (sub)Anukul Roy!! Different ways to get your name out there. He probably won't get a chance to showcase his left-arm spin this season, but Anukul Roy has pulled off a blinder as a substitute fielder. Sliced off a thick outside edge as Lomror tries to go leg-side. It goes up and behind Roy at short cover. He runs back, eyes on the ball which is going further and further away, but he races after it and dives with both hands, parallel to the ground while taking it. Stunning. Lomror c (sub)Anukul Roy b Rahul Chahar 11(13) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Boult to Samson, out Caught by Rohit!! Mumbai pacers on fire again. And not for the first time in this tournament has Samson been dismissed after being rushed on the pull. So after a great start, he's had three successive failures. The ball just comes onto him quicker than expected as he camps on the front foot. Spoons it up off the splice to mid-on. Royals losing this match in a hurry. Samson c Rohit b Boult 0(3)
